Talented Nigerian soul singer, Omafumay has revealed the idea behind her new release titled ‘Brand New’. In a recent interview, the Delta-born entertainer said this is her own bolt of lighting wrapped in a bow and she is sending it out to encourage people to stay confident and always make boss moves not allowing anything to dim their light. “I want to encourage people to live a life with no regrets. That’s why putting out this project as an independent artiste was very important to me. It’s about making boss moves and making things happen no matter the circumstance. It’s about inspiring my fans, especially the younger generation to pursue their goals fearlessly and effortlessly,” Omafumay said. Asked to shed more light about herself and how she got her stage name, “My name ‘Omafumay’ pronounced Oma-fu-may is actually my full first name which originates from Delta State and it means God has given me peace.” Nigeria Info Rewards Listeners Via Treasure Hunt Campaign Spotify EQUAL Music Programme Welcomes Nigerian Rising Star,… Speaking on factors that affect her music writing, Omafumay stated that her environment is a major influence when composing songs, “I write songs based on what is going on around me and based on how I would like to portray myself to the world. My songs subtly tell a story about my life. I’m working on bettering myself as an artiste, new music material and hopefully releasing my second single soon.” Since the release of ‘Brand New’, fans and lovers of Omafumay have been inspired to make videos of their own which have resulted in Tik Tok challenges on social media, duets, response videos and has driven the #omabrandnew community engagement.